programme.desc: Kim and her family have been frightened out of their seaside Maryland home. Multiple family members have reported sightings of children with purple lips and strange noises emanating from the nearby creek.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Spirits of the Slave Dungeon
programme.desc: Ryan books a two-night case in a real haunted jail in Charleston, SC, but PRS soon realizes the spirits themselves are being held there against their will and subjected to an unjust form of torture.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Requiem
programme.desc: A young woman named Kristy has been haunted in her own bedroom since she can remember. Now it's up to Ryan and the crew to help Kristy before she's overwhelmed by the entity.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Knickerbocker
programme.desc: PRS checks into the Knickerbocker Hotel in Linesville, Pennsylvania where the owners are reporting strange noises and the appearance of phantom children in some of the rooms.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Berkley Castle, Glouctershire
programme.desc: The murder of King Edward II features most in the 1,000 year history of this great castle. It is believed that Edward met a violent end here at Berkley. It is his ghost the team hopes to contact.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Kiplin Hall
programme.desc: Kiplin Hall was originally built as a hunting lodge in the 1620s. With generations of landowners and servants' lives revolving around this great hall, Kiplin is steeped in paranormal phenomena.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Carlisle Castle
programme.desc: Built on the site of a Roman fort, Carlisle Castle represents over nine centuries of military and royal activity. Many ghost stories have been born out of the suffering associated with this castle.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Brinkburn Priory
programme.desc: This 12th century priory is said to be haunted by the monks who lived and died there. Visions of a lady in white have also been reported. The team visits the Brinkburn Priory to investigate.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Verdley Woods
programme.desc: The team investigates the Verdley woods. Believed to have been once used by a Roman garrison, the woods have been associated with witchcraft and devil worship for many years.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Maesmawr Hall
programme.desc: Maesmawr Hall was initially a farmhouse, and was given to the Earl of Leicester as a hunting lodge by Elizabeth I. The ghostly figure of the Earl's white horse has been sighted in nearby fields.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Belsay Hall, Northumberland
programme.desc: The empty rooms of this abandoned 19th century country mansion are said to echo with the voices of phantom children when night falls. Will this children visit the team during their stay?

programme.title: Most Haunted: Gregynog Hall, Wales
programme.desc: Standing on an ancient settlement, Gregynog Hall was built entirely of concrete in 1840. Guests of the hall tell of a large man accompanied by a faithful dog that loiter by the main entrance.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Heaven on Earth
programme.desc: Mark asks Jonathan to help erase everything bad that's happened to him recently. Mark's idea is to create his own vision of heaven on Earth.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Summit
programme.desc: A dying woman was forced to leave a son behind in the Soviet Union during World War II.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Torch
programme.desc: Tragedy occurs when a Neo-Nazi disputes the Holocaust with the son of a death camp survivor.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Sail Away
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark assist a novelist who's given up. Also, they motivate the man's grandson, who has yet to tap into his literary potential.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Children's Children
programme.desc: A reporter uncovers a secret about the past of a woman who runs a home for unwed mothers.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Friends
programme.desc: While working as a substitute teacher at a high school, Jonathan assigns an overweight girl to tutor a troubled baseball star.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Special Love - Part 1
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark persuade a youngster with Down's Syndrome to join the Special Olympics.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Donna Fuller "One Year On"
programme.desc: Derby wife and mum Donna Fuller was stuck at home and stuck in a rut. Nicky revisits to see if Donna is still a woman who can pass the poll test and look 34.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Finding the Inner Girly Girl
programme.desc: Melissa Harris has devoted her life to raising her two young girls, but she's afraid she's falling short in her motherly duties. We're going to bring out the femme fatale in Melissa so she can be a super mom and role model.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Back To Glamour
programme.desc: Rebecca gets a sophisticated makeover to bring back some of the glamour from her pre-mom days. Now, her husband can recognize the girl he married, but will she look 10 Years Younger?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Fashion 911
programme.desc: Between two failed marriages, the loss of her father and caring for her ailing mother, Zoe feels life taking its toll on her appearance. She has found happiness in a new marriage, and she wants to feel confident when they are in public together.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Frizzy to Fine
programme.desc: Zina is a makeup artist by trade – a woman who encourages people to look their best to show off their spirit. However, spending all her time working and taking care of her children, Zina realizes she doesn't live by her own advice.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Emma Singh
programme.desc: Busy mum and part time student Emma Singh has a taste for the bad things in life and it shows big time on her face. Cosmetic surgeon Jan Stanek plans to get Emma to travel more lightly and youthfully by ridding Emma of her excess baggage on day one.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Viv Thomas
programme.desc: Nicky Hambleton-Jones and the team come to the rescue of 48 year old Viv Thomas.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Looking for Mr. Right
programme.desc: Ellen is looking for Mr. Right, but due to very busy work and school schedules she hasn't had any time to take care of her looks. We're going make Ellen stand out in the dating competition as we try to make her look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Programming A New Look
programme.desc: Once upon a time, Ian was a groovy party DJ with long hair, spinning disco tunes. Now he's the computer dude with long gray hair. Intense skin treatments, lasik surgery and a Glam overhaul trim 10 years from his looks.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Hard Hat to Hottie
programme.desc: Laura is a former construction worker who spent years exposed to the harsh elements. Our whole team of experts has kicked into gear to turn back the clock and transform this former construction worker from hard hat to hottie.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: I'm No Grandma
programme.desc: Kathy is a mother who has battled health setbacks while raising her kids. She wants to shake off her general malaise and look better as a first step to feeling better. Find out how Kathy goes from dreary to cheery in her journey to look ten years younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Self Conscious To Self Confident
programme.desc: Laura, a public speaker, has lost her self-confidence and is now only self-conscious. Once upbeat and bubbly, she suffered from an illness that took its toll on her appearance and self esteem. Can our experts help Laura regain her identity and a new look?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Jilly Graham
programme.desc: Nicky Hambleton-Jones and her team of age-busting experts come to the rescue of Jilly Graham from Bradford.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Work To Do
programme.desc: A successful giraffe capture means everyone is in high spirits, until the arrival of Evan and Olivia's real father, Simon, throws the family into turmoil.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Meerly Evan
programme.desc: Evan lets the mischievous meerkats loose in Rosie's room to cause havoc. Rosie is devastated when they destroy an irreplaceable photograph of her mother and rages at Evan. She decides once and for all to go back to Bristol.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Evan Meets Elli
programme.desc: Rogue young male elephants are rampaging through Leopard's Den and destroying everything the family have built, so Danny introduces a matriarch elephant in the hope that she will calm them down.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Dawn Feeling
programme.desc: At a typically rowdy family breakfast, Rosie is excitedly looking forward to the arrival of her friend Izzy, whilst Danny is concerned about the rumour of ivory poachers in the area. Unnoticed, Miranda the lion cub pads off into the bush.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: The Trevanions have been living at Leopard's Den for over a year. The wildlife is roaming freely and the family are settled into African way of life. Business however is not good. With an abundance of game lodges competition is fierce.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: It's the grand reopening of Mara and a British wildlife charity is using the event to release a vulture back into the wild. Fatani, the new, young and ambitious manager of Mara has hired Danny as the vet to oversee the release.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Leopard's Den is looking after a sick and orphaned baby elephant called Togo. However, despite Evan and Du Plessis' constant vigil, Togo is dying from a broken heart. Evan is distraught and Du Plessis promises they will look after her together.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Sarah's absence couldn't have come at a worse time for Leopard's Den. Nature Conservation is carrying out their annual inspection and everything has to be tip top. Danny's determined they pass with flying colours and everyone is roped in to help.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A young man has flipped his quad bike and can't move his neck. Later that night, the crew is called to a suburban house because a DIY homebuilder has fallen through the roof in his house – and there's a bone sticking out through his jeans.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 7
programme.desc: Young Rhys calls the embassy after his businessman father is arrested and jailed for fraud. Can Rhys raise the bail money to get him out of jail? It's a race against the clock.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 8
programme.desc: Ash contacts the embassy convinced he's going to die after days of partying. The notorious Thai bucket strikes again! The embassy needs to uncover the truth. Is he really in danger or is he suffering from alcohol poisoning?

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 1
programme.desc: Nathan is in Phuket on a holiday of a lifetime, fuelled by sun, sex and steroids, when disaster strikes. 19-year-old Paris is on a gap year adventure of a lifetime. But just two months into her first-ever overseas holiday she's hit a big roadblock.

programme.title: Perfect Vagina
programme.desc: Through our author's personal journey this documentary will explore this fascinating secret world and question what or who is fuelling women's desire to have perfect vaginas.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: De Anna and her husband were celebrating their 50th wedding anniversary on board a luxury liner. The ship's doctor radios for help. But the liner is a long way out at sea. Can the rescue crew get to De Anna in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 14 year-old motor-cross rider, Kacee gets the death wobbles and cartwheels over the top of his handle bars and hits the ground head first. He's now struggling to breath and is barely able to talk. Team Air Rescue needs to get Kacee to the hospital fast.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Mountain bike fanatic, Blake was out riding when he clipped a tree and crashed into a rock. It's a time critical rescue mission. And what the rescue crew doesn't yet know is that Blake is about to take a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: The Car of the Future
programme.desc: The car of the future - this is how it might look: Aerodynamic, light and quiet. And with almost no fuel consumption. This is how we could soon travel on roads. But is a car like this just a pipe dream of engineers?

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Isle of Mann TT 2015 Documentary
programme.desc: The Tourist Trophy on the British Isle of Man is the most famous motorcycle race in the world. TT Sidecar champion Klaus Klaffenböck and racing expert Lenz Leberkern explore the fascination behind the TT Isle of Man.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Vintage Airplane Show Days
programme.desc: In this special report Motorvision TV will not be on tour on the streets, but in the air and will pay a tribute to the history of motorized aviation. One of the oldest airfields in Germany is located at Oberschleissheim near Munich.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Germany´s Supercar Rally
programme.desc: On Saturday the 11th of July 2015, owners and co-drivers of 450 supercars flocked at Germany's Bielefeld to join the biggest supercar rally ever organized in Europe so far.

programme.title: On Tour: Night of the Jumps
programme.desc: Munich, the Olympic Arena at the Night of the Jumps. These young guys will make the arena shake. They are fearless, and are going to really let it rip today. The biggest motor cross freestyle event in the world!

programme.title: On Tour: Bus Stunts with Action Concept
programme.desc: We are going to take you behind the scenes of the movie industry. We are here with Action Concept, Europe's most successful film production company, testing a stunt with a twelve ton bus going to be sent into the air.

programme.title: On Tour: ADAC Bavaria Historic Rallye
programme.desc: A lot is going on in front of Castle Maxlrain at Bad Aibling, Germany. 20 000 visitors have gathered at the ADAC Bavaria Historic Rallye to see the most beautiful classical cars.

programme.title: On Tour: Truck Grand Prix am Nuerburgring
programme.desc: Today we are for Europe's biggest truck race event. It is the international ADAC Truck Grand Prix at the Nürburgring.

programme.title: On Tour: DTM Racing in Munich
programme.desc: We are here live at the first ever big DTM showevent in Munich. The motors are getting hot and ready to run. Just in a few moments we are listening to the sound of 470 hp V8-engines of the DTM racing cars.

programme.title: On Tour: Fun at the BMW Enduro Park
programme.desc: Today it's going to be dirty and dusty because we are at the BMW Enduro Park in Hechlingen.
programme.sub-title: Fun at the BMW Enduro Park

programme.title: On Tour: Bike and Music Weekend
programme.desc: The Bike and Music Weekend is one of the most spectacular events for motor vehicle fans. Every summer, thousands of bikers and motorcycle fans from all over the world meet in Geiselwind, Germany, to show off their vehicles, and to have fun.

programme.title: On Tour: 125 Years Mercedes
programme.desc: Berlin-Tempelhof Airport. But no longer used as an airport. A historical monument. Not without reason, Mercedes Benz chose this historic location to celebrate their 125th birthday.

programme.title: On Tour: BMW M1 Meeting
programme.desc: The Austrian racing scene is now richer by one attraction, having added the Histo Cup Austria. 10.000 motor racing fans make their way to the Salzburgring in Austria to admire over 200 historical race cars in action.
